üëâ Write class structure (Java / pseudo-code).

2Ô∏è‚É£ OVERRIDING vs HIDING (TRAP ‚ö†Ô∏è)
class Notification {
    void send() {
        System.out.println("Sending notification");
    }

    static void log() {
        System.out.println("Logging notification");
    }
}

class EmailNotification extends Notification {
    void send() {
        System.out.println("Sending email");
    }

    static void log() {
        System.out.println("Logging email");
    }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Notification n = new EmailNotification();
        n.send();
        n.log();
    }
}


üëâ What will be the output and WHY?
Explain like an interviewer expects (compile time vs runtime).

